'''Flukonazole''' is an antifungal medication that is given either by mouth or intravenously.  It is used to treat a variety of fungal infections, especially ''Candida'' infections of the vagina, mouth, throat, and bloodstream. 

It is on the World Health Organization's (Mokgatlo wa Maphelo wa Lefase) List of Essential Medicines, a list of the most important medication needed in a basic health system.
